{
  "texts": [
    "It uses the discrete wavelet transform (DWT) in conjunction with a complex DEV-22 CNN model and a support vector machine (SVM).",
    "This cyclical trend demonstrates that these CADx systems are becoming progressively more sophisticated; each new model enhances the diagnostic accuracy and reliability of colorectal cancer detection by leveraging the capabilities of the systems that preceded it.",
    "The bar chart in Fig. 19 illustrates a comparison of the results.",
    "The proposed PolyNetDWTCADx framework has shown that it is capable of achieving an remarkable accuracy of 92.3%, hence proving its potentials in balancing performance, interpretability, and computational efficiency.",
    "Unlike previous models that bank on complex architectures or the ensemble, this framework was optimally integrating DEV-22 and Discrete Wavelet Transform-DWT with SVM for superior extraction, refinement, and classifying features."
  ]
}